						<div class="postbody">Oh, i see. Well, it has a nice substance to it, when it's either because of (like in this case), or based on a real process, like decompressing and uploading tiles.  <img src="./images/smilies/Mfr_icon_homebrew.png" alt=":beer:" title="Beer" />  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  For comparison, many &quot;text scrambler&quot; effects for appearing/disappearing text i've seen used in animation/sfx seem to just take a seed and dish out some RND product based on that and the current frame. I think random functions often feel a little cheap/superficially imposed; because they often are. Such can be done with AfterEffects scripts, but there's also commercial plugins for the same for those who don't have the time. Sorry for the side note.</div>

					
